reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Update: The company reached out to me and sent me a new bag free of charge after the return window had passed. Great customer service. This new bag has held up much better than the first one I received. I've been using it consistently for over a month now with no signs of the stitching failing. See below for the original 1 start review.The interior stitching on the inside where you place your shoes is subpar. It ripped only after 2 weeks of putting shoes in/out. This makes the shoe storage section useless as it opens it up to the rest of the interior storage. I was lazy and just got around to reviewing this and missed the return window by 2 days. The rest of the bag is decent but now I'll have to buy a separate bag to keep my shoes/wet clothes in. I'd spend the extra money on a name brand bag.

reviews.reviewText: Love this gym bag it's got enough space to hold all of my belongings. The zipper is comically oversized but that's the look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Upon initial inspection the bag arrived with every regular sized zipper off track. It was strange to see but easy enough to fix. Unfortunately, I located another spot near the skull where the colored material had a small tear and was beginning to flake off the bag itself. I’m super bummed out because the idea looks awesome but the execution is terrible. Also, not sure why but it arrives with a terrible synthetic odor. Like a REALLY strong plastic/rubber type odor that has not gone away and it’s been out for over 24hrs. Shame. This bag really could have been great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Bag I have
reviews.reviewText: I really love this bag. The zipper is super cool, and at the gym it's hilarious how many people are like "is that really the zipper". The bag is very durable and feels like a solid product. The compartments are easy to get to and the size is perfect. The shoe stash is great and I keep an extra pair in their just in case. Love taking this to the gym and I have had a few people stop me and go on Amazon for me to show them where it is. Great bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Different sort of gym bag with most of the essential pockets one needs
reviews.reviewText: Well I have not used the bag yet, so I am unable to provide it with 5 stars, or even a proper review when it comes to anything more than my initial impression. With that being said, there are a few things I enjoy about this bag that I find compelling to share. It has a shoe compartment, a feature I find critical to a gym bag. Seems to be large enough to hold a pair of clothes, shower materials, shoes, shaker bottle, and a snack. The material, although pleather, which does wear out and is honestly a terrible material in general, feels good when it’s fresh. I don’t care much for the logo or the name being written on the side of the bag, but I also won’t take a star away from the review due to my own personal taste. The oversized zipper is ridiculous, it makes a ton of unnecessary noise and is somewhat pointless. However it is a good conversation piece, and you know you are not going to mistakenly zip up something in your bag, poking a hole into a Cotten shirt or something of this nature like you may with an overpacked back containing a smaller sized zipper.Pretty pleased so far but only time will tell the truth about this bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love the bag overall. The compartments, the space, the quality. EXCEPT for the main zipper. It broke after the first use. It is way too big in my opinion and very cheap. I just use the buckels to hold the opening closed. The bag would be 10/10 for me with a nicer quality or at least smaller zipper.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars My new favorite bag (UPDATE: No longer my fav)
reviews.reviewText: I have been looking for a a gym bag to replace my current one for long while. I’ve looked online & gone to sporting stores but I was looking for something very specific. I was even ready to give up on the fabric design as long as I had the specs I wanted. This has everything. It’s really aesthetically appealing for the gym (I got pink), 2 zipper pockets on the inside, a shoe compartment, sturdy fabric, pockets on the outside & a zipper bigger than I’ve ever seen before that I never have to worry about getting stuck. All the straps are well secured also. Most of my complaints about the other bags is that the bottom didn’t have any kind of padding or extra layer to it. This fabric is so thick & because this doubles as a backpack, the bottoms/back, has padding.I would say that my only complaint is that the straps attach way far on the sides causing the bag to collapse & fold in when you carry it on one shoulder but I still LOVE it. I never have used my gym bag for anything other than the gym but I will start using this as an overnight bag as well… or maybe buy another one. I wish they made more colors like a mint green. I’d buy it today.UPDATE: Per my intial review, I was wrong about the straps being durable. My bag never weighs more than 15 pounds max and that is usually because of a pair of shoes and a water bottle and not even a big water bottle. I keep a pair of sweats, a towel, and then the small essentials (headphones, workout gloves, deodorant, gum, etc.). The straps started pulling apart from the bag so I tried using gorilla glue and that didn’t work so then I used shoe repair cement and that helped a little bit as you can see it’s still falling apart. And even though I don’t have anything sharp or heavy in my bag, the side pocket seam ripped and because of the material I can’t sew it. I’m really disappointed in this bag. I wanted to love it. Now it is back to looking for another that’s actually worth the money.
Zipper is a bit too big haha but the bag is perfect for gym workouts where you're in and out of the bag.
